  "title": "Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description &amp; Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>• Knowledge ofengineering fundamentals and practices</p>\n<p>• Ability to draft and design plans and schematics</p>\n<p>• Strong analytical and problem-solving skills</p>\n<p>• Technical project management skills and experience</p>\n<p>• Excellent communication skills</p>\n<p>• Ability to design and test systems</p>\n<p>• Knowledge of the latest trends and technologies</p>\n<p> Engineers are tasked with several key responsibilities that ensure the efficiency and safety of systems. </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>These include:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Designing, developing, and testing electrical equipment and systems, focusing on safety, efficiency, and reliability.</li>\n  <li>Analyzing  systems and components to identify hazards, defects, or the need for adjustment or repair, and to ensure compliance with codes.</li>\n  <li>Directing and coordinating manufacturing, construction, installation, maintenance, support, documentation, and testing activities to ensure compliance with specifications, codes, and customer requirements.</li>\n  <li>Performing detailed calculations to establish standards and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Using computer-assisted engineering and design software and equipment to perform engineering tasks.</li>\n  <li>Preparing specifications for purchases of all type of equipment and materials.</li>\n  <li>Supervising or training project team members as necessary.</li>\n  <li>Estimating material, labor, or construction costs for budget preparation purposes.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>To qualify for a position as an Engineer, candidates must meet specific educational and certification standards:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>No formal Education is required.</li>\n</ul>",
